Model D

Create the analysis ready dataframe that can be used for both model D and model E. * The filter of ageYear!='0-19' is because there is one event in this category, which messes up the fit. We require >5 events in all categories. This is just a simple ad-hoc way around this, instead of regrouping and/or redefining categories.

pc.modelDE.df <- eavehelpers::serology_outcome_analysis.create_hosp_death_dataframe(data.pc,eave.data) %>% code_vars() %>% filter(ageYear!='0-19')

pc.modelE.df %>% group_by(igg,outcome_hosp) %>% summarise(n=n())

`summarise()` has grouped output by 'igg'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.

Calculate a formular that will calculate the number of risks groups expect for four specific risk groups

qnames <- pc.modelE.df %>% eavehelpers::get_qcovid_names(var='outcome_hosp',condition=1,n=1)
qnames2 <- c("Q_DIAG_BLOOD_CANCER","Q_DIAG_CHD","Q_DIAG_PULM_HYPER","Q_DIAG_COPD")
formula_other <- paste0(paste0(qnames,collapse = ' + ')," - ",paste0(qnames2,collapse = ' - '))
formula_other
[1] "Q_DIAG_CKD_LEVEL + Q_DIAG_AF + Q_DIAG_ASTHMA + Q_DIAG_BLOOD_CANCER + Q_DIAG_CCF + Q_DIAG_CHD + Q_DIAG_CIRRHOSIS + Q_DIAG_CONGEN_HD + Q_DIAG_COPD + Q_DIAG_DEMENTIA + Q_DIAG_DIABETES_1 + Q_DIAG_EPILEPSY + Q_DIAG_FRACTURE + Q_DIAG_NEURO + Q_DIAG_PULM_HYPER + Q_DIAG_PULM_RARE + Q_DIAG_PVD + Q_DIAG_RA_SLE + Q_DIAG_STROKE + Q_DIAG_VTE - Q_DIAG_BLOOD_CANCER - Q_DIAG_CHD - Q_DIAG_PULM_HYPER - Q_DIAG_COPD"
pc.modelE.df <- pc.modelE.df %>%
  mutate_at(vars(contains("Q_DIAG")),~as.numeric(ifelse(.=='Yes',1,0))) %>%
  mutate(n_risk_gpsOther = !!parse_quo(formula_other, env = caller_env())) %>%
  mutate(n_risk_gpsOther = as.factor(ifelse(n_risk_gpsOther>2,'3+',n_risk_gpsOther))) %>% 
  mutate_at(vars(contains("Q_DIAG")),~as.factor(ifelse(.==1,'Yes','No'))) 
formula <- paste0("Surv(t1,t2, outcome_hosp) ~ igg + additional  + ",
                              paste0(qnames2,collapse=" + "),
                              "+ n_risk_gpsOther + ageYear + Sex + Q_BMI " )
pc.modelE.cox <- with(pc.modelE.df,coxph(as.formula(formula)))
